Subject: [PATCH] Wire up recommend.py; combine ticket/desc/report into one
 copy
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Recommend.py wiring (#1):
- recommend.py expected fields (case_id, case_date, root_cause_raw,
  resolution_raw, recurrence_flag) that don't exist in case_history's
  real schema (id, date, error_fault, solution, no root_cause or
  recurrence tracking). Added the missing columns + case_history_fts,
  plus db.search_similar() and db.notes_for() to match recommend.py's
  expected interface, rather than rewriting its ranking logic.
- server.py /api/parse now calls recommend.diagnose() per block and
  returns confidence-scored root causes + resolutions + supporting
  past cases under 'recommend'.
- UI: new 'Similar past cases' panel (evidence strength, ranked
  causes/resolutions with confidence %, supporting case snippets).
  Empty until cases are actually saved — this builds up over time,
  not on first use.
- Save Case form: added Root cause + 'Fault recurred' fields so
  future recommendations have cause/success data to weight on.
- tests/test_recommend.py: 6 tests covering search_similar, notes_for,
  diagnose() end-to-end, no-data safety, and recurrence down-weighting.

One-click OneNote copy:
- Copy button now assembles ticket number(s) + the original raw paste
  (verbatim) + the report into one block, instead of copying the
  report alone. Removes the separate manual paste of ticket
  number/fault description into OneNote before pasting the report.
